{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP","text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The tint to apply.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"tint"}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a given styling. Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overridden by user preference, tint is always respected and should","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be used as a way to provide additional meaning to the control.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls which are unable to style themselves using the given type of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" will try to approximate the styling as best as they can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. controls which can not style themselves using a gradient will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attempt to use the color of the gradient’s first stop)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows a linear gauge tinted with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"gradient from ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/blue","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/red","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["struct ControlTint: View {","    var body: some View {","        Gauge(value: 75, in: 0...100) {","            Text(\"Temperature\")","        }","        .gaugeStyle(.linearCapacity)","        .tint(Gradient(colors: [.blue, .orange, .red]))","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some controls adapt to the tint color differently based on their style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current platform, and the surrounding context. For example, in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS, a button with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/bordered"},{"type":"text","text":" style doesn’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tint its background, but one with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/borderedProminent"},{"type":"text","text":" style does. In macOS, neither"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of these button styles tint their label, but they do in other platforms."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/timelineview\/tint(_:)-4c5ho"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Sets the tint within this view.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/TimelineView\/tint(_:)-4c5ho","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/TimelineView"]]},"metadata":{"title":"tint(_:)","remoteSource":{"fileName":"Tint.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/Tint.swift#L47"},"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE4tintyQrqd__SgAA10ShapeStyleRd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:11OpenSwiftUI12TimelineViewV","role":"symbol","modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/TimelineView":{"fragments":[{